	<div class="commentbody">
      <p>omg, no&#8230;  But I&#8217;m sure that Cisco wished your statement were true!<br />
<a href="http://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/routers/access/800/rcsi/800srcsi.html#wp113562" rel="nofollow">http://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/routers/access/800/rcsi/800srcsi.html#wp113562</a></p>
<p>The antenna power can be anything, based on antenna gain, directionality and bandwidth, but the radiated power measured at 3m can&#8217;t be above the limit lines.  Otherwise, the remaining electronics in a household would be in a world of hurt!  ;&gt;</p>

