	<div class="commentbody">
      <p>I did some research of my own, and I&#8217;ve uncovered some things, which give some clues but nothing definitive.</p>
<p>(1) There is a Paul McArthur who is a co-inventor on a patent for an &#8216;article locator system&#8217;, first filed in 2002 (12 years ago!). <a href="http://www.freepatentsonline.com/6788199.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.freepatentsonline.com/6788199.html</a> </p>
<p>(2) The first inventor of that patent is Timothy Crabtree, and the assignee is Eureka Technology Partners, LLC. Tim is the founder of Eureka Technology Partners. <a href="http://eurekaproducts.com/about/" rel="nofollow">http://eurekaproducts.com/about/</a> </p>
<p>(3) Eureka Technology Partners&#8217; existing product tracks pets, using tags. <a href="http://eurekaproducts.com/about/" rel="nofollow">http://eurekaproducts.com/about/</a> </p>
<p>(4) Note the similarities between Eureka&#8217;s product and the iFind, namely the limited charging requirements</p>

